caption: Good variety, good food.
I constantly come by getting some food here. I love the swift customer service and well prepared food. Kudos.
This place always delivers. They have excellent dishes for reasonable prices, there no long wait even when the place is packed.
Ramen was inedible, might as well just inject pure salt into your veins.

I was VERY disappointed with the sushi here. It was too expensive for the portion sizes. The fish was not particularly fresh so the rolls didn't taste good. I got three small maki rolls that fit into 1 takeout container that cost about $45.  There are much better sushi places in the Montgomery county area so I most likely will not be coming back here. However, it will do in a pinch if you are in downtown Bethesda and craving sushi asap.
Sushi were great but the takeout waiting time was not. I called, they said 40 min, but when I came I had to wait another 30!

I just want to say that I ordered sushi for lunch here, and I have 0 complaints. Arguably some of the best sushi I have had in my life. The spicy Mayo wasn’t overly Mayo-y, the portions were decent and all the ingredients blended perfectly. Will be ordering again!

I went to Hanaro Sushi with my friends for dinner and we LOVED it! All the staff were wearing masks and greeted us warmly. Our server, Tina, was very attentive, friendly, and gave us amazing recommendations. The sushi quality was amazing— so fresh and delicious. Highly recommend coming here!

Hanaro has great sushi but the takeout experience is horrible. The wait times they estimate are wildly low; waited 40 minutes outside for the last order. When I arrived it was clear that they hadn’t even started making about it... or thinking about it. And I wasn’t the only one; there were many people going through the same thing. And the servers aren’t even a little apologetic. They need to figure out their takeout logistics because the last experience was enough to keep me from ordering there.

Hanaro Sushi's Cuisine and Service is Exceptional.  Morgan Provides Shocking Levels of Diner Service. Morgan is quite comfortable making recommendations to select from the menu. Like, The Goyza (Japanese Dumpling) is on the menu as fried or Steamed and Morgan suggested Pan Seared and it was a Home Run. Also, check out the "Fresh Wasabi" (A Must).  We always get the Fried Rice as an entree, as the portion is large and quite good and supports all of our Sushi selections. Same goes for the Tator Tots. The starter is topped with Pork belly, Scallions, Spicy Mayo and Bonito Flakes. The dish was delicious and quite filling.  You may want to have some cash on-hand, as the all tips placed on your credit card goes to the house and the servers see a % far less than what you anticipated.  You will definitely enjoy your dining experience.  RichandJames Peterson
Long wait for pick up

Excellent sushi, fresh and beautifully prepared. I cannot speak to their spicy -anything- rolls or their other entrees. Appetizers hit the spot but are pricey.  Seared salmon belly nigiri is actually perfect. I really enjoyed their nigiri combos as well. Top notch customer service. Really great ordering through Door Dash while I'm at work. I love them and their sister restaurants Kusshi and Poke Dojo; all lovely for people who really enjoy real sushi. I also love that they offer deals occasionally through Chow Now, thanks!!
The beef in the dish was tough as a shoe, dumplings cold, teriyaki was good. Not consistent enough for me a $60.00 carry out bill.

I had the best delivery order from a sushi restaurant I have ever had:  crispy, warm soft shell crabs (2), eel, avocado, rice, cucumber roll (6 pieces) and unusual yum, light dessert, ice cream in a hard tempera shell.  I'll be back

Holy smokes, I would rate this on the same level as grocery store sushi. My sister got spicy tuna, spicy salmon and spicy scallop all with tempura crunch.  The temperature flakes were  stale and looks like the leftovers  you got from frying shrimp tempura instead of making the batter and frying it solely to make tempura flakes. These were probably fried a few days ago or improperly stored to remove air/moisture from the product.  The baked Cali was overly fishy and a bit on the dry side considering the description has Kewpie mayo. Rice was a bit on the dry side. Just a bad experience. Will not be returning.
came here with my grandma, looked like a nice place and had good food but when I had ordered they took my grandma and threw her out the window and spit in my drink

We like a lot going out. Last night we  visited this delicious restaurant which friends told us about. We enjoyed a delightful time there with great food and  an experienced crew and a great cook. We  added this venue in our phone list  and we shall definitely come back soon. We warmly recommend.
the food and setting was great but i was attacked by a racist karen whilst trying to park and she called the police!

Two and a half hours late! We have had their sushi before with no problems and in general it was good quality.  However, our last order to them was delivered 2.5 hrs late.  We tried calling them when the order was just 30 mins late, but they never picked up the phone.  We made four more attempts to contact them, but they never picked up our calls.  After being an hour and half late we gave up and ate PBJs.  Their delivery came 2 and a half hours sfter promised delivery time.
Good food, but they're not managing the take-out only process very effectively at all.

Ordered popular items and picked up. The food was eatable but so plain, boring, not tasty, missing spicy souses. Was very disappointed and will never order again, especially the price was not matching to the quality.
Awesome sushi and cool atmosphere!

This restaurant is my favored. I visit many restaurants but to this place I  constantly return again and again. The crew is very welcoming and the food they place on your table is so flavorful. I would always prefer to have a decent meal in this place. I highly recommend this place.

From the moment we walked in we t hmm ought we should leave but well...we were hungry and had a Groupon. The music was so loud even if you weren't sitting in the bar area and the pounding bass was pretty crazy. The small plates on our table were full of black dust and when our waitress replaced them one of the new plates had food on it. When we received our drinks one glass had lipstick on it from the last guest. Well finally it's time to eat and while the selection was nice, the flavor was simply nonexistent. The sushi looked beautiful and creative but just simply had no flavor. The staff was simply indifferent to everything, no greeting, no checking back with us, just taking of order and delivery...that is all. Will not return even with Groupon
Good food and location.
You need a new host, she was indiferent and rude. Didn't enjoy my visit.
Food is mediocre, service was horrible.
Best sushi place I've been to in Bethesda in recent memory.

I don’t come to Bethesda very often, but I came up for the Hello Kitty wine tasting event. The staff seemed indifferent and didn’t even greet me when I came in, leaving me standing in the doorway until I just decided to walk over to the table where the wines were. The event itself was fun, but since I had come so far out of my way I had wanted to order sushi or some sort of small plates before going home. I went to the hostess and explained I wanted to order food and asked if I could be seated, the hostess waved me away saying, “you can order at the bar.” I proceeded to stand at the bar for about 20 minutes and though multiple people passed by me and looked at me, not one person acknowledged me,  even when I was attempting to flag someone down. I finally gave up and left because apparently no one wanted to accept my money. I was quite angry for the rest of the night because  like I said, I don’t live near Bethesda and it was nearly an hour drive to get home after not receiving the sushi dinner I had been wanting. Disappointed, especially since it looked so good.

This site is my first choice restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I love it most. Finally decided to leave and servers spoke their only words to us “thanks! Have a good night!” Blood was boiling - I will never go back.

I was there last weekend and was not greeted by the female greeter. She had no respect, and she was on her phone texting while I was talking to her. She has a bad attitude as well. Even though the food was great, I will never go there again. I hope the manager solves this problem.

Walked in and was not greeted by the African American female greeter who lacked proper manners. Picked up an order and the place was mostly empty. There was a Latino server who had a bad attitude as well. The atmosphere in this place was less than appealing.

From the moment  you arrive in this restaurant  the stuff gives you an enjoyable feeling. Very friendly waiters, it is a happy restaurant to  enjoy with your friends or with your date. heavenly  cuisine, creative  chef de cuisine, decent  pay and attentive  service. Warmly recommended.

Well being from California I can be pretty snobby about sushi.  We took a chance based on the yelp reviews and happy we did. All of the food was fresh and tasty. My daughter and I shared a variety of items (we did stay basic in case) and my husband who doesn’t eat sushi at all got teriyaki chicken, Shelley our server was  GREAT, super attentive and accommodating. We had 2 special requests for our meal and she  took care of both of them no problem. The drinks got refilled fast and the table was cleared fast too. We would defiantly come back if we are in town again.  To top it off they carry the best mochi I have ever had!!!

Reserved the restaurant with a large group(~40 people) to celebrate a medical school graduation. the food was delicious (ordered several sushi boats, dumplings, fried rice, spicy shrimp and more!). I especially enjoyed the spicy shrimp and eel rolls. There was a great variety of food--anyone can eat here, even those who are apprehensive about eating raw fish! Drinks were mixed well--bartenders were worked hard but very attentive all afternoon. Owner and staff were amazing and helped everything run smoothly--thank you Hanaro, we will be back when we are back in DC!

It was a cold rainy day so I stopped for Udon. Because of the art festival and mothers day, the place was very busy and the servers were working very hard!  I had a bowl of udon and thought it was very good. The flavor of the broth was very nice and there were a lot of vegetables, which I really liked. The chicken was lightly floured and seasoned. Service was good though they were busy, the servers never stopped moving and grabbing orders and helping customers. The restaurant was very pretty and had good ambiance.  The table across from mine ordered several plates of sushi, and the waitress let them know she had charged it as a platter, since they ordered all of the same things that came on a platter. I thought it was very thoughtful of her to go out of her way to help a couple and their mothers on mother's day even though it was so busy. I was very impressed.  I had a really nice lunch and would like to come back to try the sushi sometime!

caption: Hanero is one of the best locally owned sushi places in the DMV. I regularly am willing to commute a half hour from College Park to eat sushi here. Their Omakase makes for a great night out and is perfect for anyone who likes sushi and wants a truly great experience. The food, atmosphere, and overall experience is exceptional. I eat a lot of sushi and can honestly say Hanero is one of the best places I have been to, especially if you are looking for a unique Omakase experience.

It looks like an ordinary Japanese / sushi restaurant. However I have experienced the tastiest Japanese and poke food here. The green tea is very light. You have to ask them to bring it a bit stronger. I have not tried their other drinks. They have a separate poke menu that allows you to create your own poke Bowl which I highly recommend. I have tried almost every item on the menu and I have never been disappointed. the food is made very tasty  and authentic. I come here often and I have brought many different friends and everyone has loved it here. The food is fantastic and the service is Pleasant. I highly recommend this place if you are up for some tasty food.
Great menu, large portions, awesome staff and a convenient location in Bethesda! Well worth the visit :)

One of my favorite spots. I love the food the owners and the bar tenders/ waitresses (Lilly is a real sweetheart and always welcoming) .

Quite possibly the worst sushi I've ever had. We got a sashimi sampler and had to take guesses about what was what. Some sort of list or labeling would have really helped. However, the quality of the fish was abysmal. Every piece was chewy, making trying to take just a bite impossible. Two rolls we ordered had spicy tuna, which was essentially tasteless. Much like the sashimi, the fish in the salmon rolls was chewy. The only good item in our meal was the pickled ginger. We ordered for four, but were only given two pairs of chopsticks. The rolls were small, coming with 6 pieces as opposed to the standard 8. When ordering online, we were not given all of the options for items listed in the menu itself. Here's to hoping we don't get food poisoning.

Placed a to-go order online via their website. I received an email saying what time my order would be ready for pick up- it was not ready for another 10 minutes (an inconvenience when trying to park/pull over on a busy street.) We ordered the mixed nigiri 15 piece along with 6 maki rolls and not one piece of fish was tender- all were chewy beyond belief! On top of that, one of the pieces of nigiri was just rice and roe! The spicy tuna was no flavor and minimal spice, the seaweed was chewy, and the sushi fell apart while eating it. I’m absolutely baffled as to how this restaurant has so many positive reviews. We will not be back here.

food quality is okay. but you can get groupon for discount.

Great place. The food is delicious and the service is good. I usually order to go and they are super fast. I always order the poke bowl and love it.

Extemely poor management. Everybody is all over the place, food takes HOURS as if they are picking up the rice from the rice fields and making the damn sushi from scratch. Music is extremely loud at times, it kinda gives a ghetto vibe. There is one guy specifically that looks like he hates his life, extremely rude. I hope the higher ups read the reviews and try to improve customer service.
Great service and lunch specials

Would give a 4.5 if I had the option. Took my mother here for her birthday along with my sister, fiancé, and grandmother! We got a sushi boat that included nigiri, sashimi, and 3 rolls of our choice. I liked that we had some say in what kind of rolls we wanted as in other restaurants you usually just have to trust in the chef’s choice! The boat was beautifully presented and the service was amazing and friendly, however I do feel that they put way too much rice in the nigiri. My fiancé and I have traveled in japan for a total of 2 months and are avid sushi eaters so we may just be a bit picky but some of the fish did not taste super fresh (not atypical at all for the area though so I’m not really holding it against them). My sister got the seafood udon which was the most decked out seafood udon I have ever seen. Very generous with the amount of seafood!

The staff was amazing, only two girls waiting on the entire place and they did a great job. The food tasted good. The seafood was fresh. We really enjoyed the tempura. All in all, a nice place for fresh sushi.

Such a nice gem in Bethesda. They have great food and service with very nice and caring workers.  I initially came here with some friends for one of their Mochi events that I saw a Facebook event for. Even though I'm allergic to this stuff (dairy), I still came. The mochi that was being distributed around looked sooo good. I wanted to try a piece but I would have had to go to the hospital lol. They were the perfect iced and smooth texture. I could see from my friend's faces that they were enjoying every single bite.  While I was there, I ordered one of their ramen. It came out super fast and was quite filling for me. It came with pork, seaweed, egg, and I think bamboo shoots (not really sure what they were ). Needless to say, it exceeded my expectations. Because it came out so fast, I thought they might have half-assed my meal. But nope, it was cooked and prepared just right. It was hot with a salty flavor and a somewhat thick texture to it. I love eggs in ramen and this was no different.  The restaurant is also very modern to the younger generation while being very inclusive to an older crowd. They play a combination of chill, energetic, and hip music in the background. Which makes me feel great eating there. The workers also seem to have a good time.  Splendid food, service, workers, and atmosphere. I will definitely be back.
Best sushi in Bethesda

I stepped into Hanaro Restaurant with the intention to attend a Complimentary Sake Tasting but I ended having dinner here too. My parents and I ordered items from the regular dinner menu as well as items off the Naka Zima Specials menu and Happy Hour food and drink specials. If you love raw fish and/or a spicy touch, you'd probably think Hanaro got one of the best happy hours in town.  For dinner, we ordered the following: Seaweed Salad, Lava Roll, Yellowtail and Scallion Roll, Spider Roll, California Roll, and a 18 piece sashimi.  The Lava Roll consisted of crabmeat maki topped with chopped sashimi (e.g., scallop, smoked salmon, white tuna, shrimp, and avocado) and baked in Japanese mayonnaise. It was served with crispy tempura fritters and two types of spicy sauce (e.g., spicy mayo, Sriracha). Despite asking for the spicy stuff on the side, it was much hotter than what I have ordered at New Tokyo.  The Yellowtail and Scallion Roll consisted of six yellowtail rolls topped with thinly chopped scallion.  The Spider Roll consisted of soft shell crab tempura, avocado, and cucumber rolls topped with masago and eel sauce.  By the time we finished the rolls, it was time for the complimentary sake tasting. We got to try 7 different kinds of sake. My favorites included Dassai that was served at 2016 States Dinner, Kikusui Funaguchi Honjozo, Ikezo Peach Sparkling Jelly Sake, and Yuzu Lilly Yuzu Tini (a blend of Yuzu (citrus flavored) liqueur and shoju).  After the sake tasting, we enjoyed our 18 piece sashimi which consisted of chef's selection of fresh raw fish including octopus, white fish, white tuna, salmon, red tuna, and yellowtail.  I plan on returning to Hanaro Restaurant in the near future!
